  "description": "The refrigerator from the well-known manufacturer of household appliances LG belongs to the middle price segment and is a spacious, practical, multifunctional model for a large family. The total usable volume is 341 liters, with the largest part (234 liters) occupied by the refrigerator compartment. There is everything you need for the proper organization of your workspace: 4 shelves made of durable tempered glass, a retractable container (freshness zone) for storing herbs, vegetables and fruits, an egg tray, side shelves for placing bottles and LED lighting. DoorCooling+ technology implies the presence of ventilation holes in the front part, and Multi Air Flow means the circulation of cold air throughout the chamber. These technologies provide fast, even cooling and help keep food fresh longer. At the bottom of the LG GW-B459SQLM there is a freezer with a volume of 107 liters. It is equipped with several pull-out containers and a separate Big Freezing Zone for storing meat and fish. The freezer is capable of freezing up to 12 kg of food per day and has an express freezing function. In general, in the event of a power outage, the refrigerator is able to maintain the optimal temperature for 16 hours. The inverter compressor Smart Inverter is responsible for the high performance of the device, the main advantages of which are quiet operation (noise level is 36 dB), durability and energy efficiency (class A++). Thanks to LG Total No Frost technology, users will not have to defrost either the refrigerator or freezer. In addition, the advantages of the model include the possibility of reversing the doors, a door closed indicator, voltage control technology (the refrigerator continues to operate at changes from 187 to 253 Volts) and LG Smart Diagnosis technology - diagnosing problems using a smartphone, without calling a technician.",
